posts.name: 5-8 Club
posts.note: 5-8 Club is a local tavern chain serving cheese-stuffed burgers, pub grub, and more in laid-back surrounds and the “Home of the Juicy Lucy.” NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Gandhi Mahal Restaurant
posts.note: Gandhi Mahal Restaurant is an Indian spot serving sustainable, seasonal fare with a lunch buffet and live music in homey surrounds.

posts.name: George and the Dragon
posts.note: George and the Dragon is a low-key bar with craft beers on tap along with pub grub such as fried fare and sandwiches.

posts.name: The Herbivorous Butcher
posts.note: The Herbivorous Butcher serves fully cooked, meat-free 'meats' and 'cheeses' are the specialty of this family-owned vegan market. I have heard you should order the Roasted Turkey sandwich which contains vegan turkey and vegan Dill Havarti cheese or the Vegan Italian Cold Cut sandwich which contains vegan Pastrami, vegan Capicola ham, vegan pepperoni, and vegan Mozzarella cheese. From their website, 'We have carefully crafted 100% vegan, cruelty-free meat and cheese alternatives that capture the best flavors, textures, and nutrients most people are used to without their negative impacts on health, animals, and the environment.'

posts.name: Holy Land
posts.note: Holy Land is a Middle Eastern deli attached to a market offering traditional from-scratch eats, and a lunch buffet. You need to order the hummus, pita, and falafel or the chicken shwarma.

posts.name: Lions Tap
posts.note: Lions Tap is a long-standing hangout serving draft beer and a small menu of classic burgers and sides since 1980. Lions Tap serves the classic ideal of a burger (described as a 'purist's favorite' on the menu). They serve quarter-pound patties that are ground and hand-formed daily.

posts.name: Lucky Cricket
posts.note: Lucky Cricket is a created by Andrew Zimmern and Michael McDermott, they focus on small plates, sharable foods, and adventurous culinary experiences utilizing natural, organic, and local ingredients, served in a contemporary atmosphere that also features a world-class Tiki bar experience.

posts.name: Matt's Bar and Grill
posts.note: Matt's Bar and Grill is a circa-1954, cash-only beer and burger joint celebrated for its cheese-stuffed patty, the Jucy Lucy.

posts.name: Pig Ate My Pizza
posts.note: Pig Ate My Pizza is a high-energy pizza joint serving imaginative pies and draft beers amid pig-themed decor.

posts.name: Salty Tart
posts.note: Salty Tart is a charming choice in the Midtown Global Market for arsenal sweet and savory pastries, fresh breads, and cakes. It means seasonal, local and organic ingredients are used whenever possible. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Spoon and Stable
posts.note: Spoon and Stable is a hip pick for a French-inspired menu in a cozy, rustic-chic vintage carriage house.

posts.name: Surly Brewing Company
posts.note: Surly Brewing Company is a bustling venue with tavern grub and their own microbrews, plus an upstairs eatery with beer pairings and pizza.

posts.name: Victor's 1959 Cafe
posts.note: Victor's 1959 Cafe has signatures and doodles of former guests adorning walls at this snug Cuban cafe with patio seating.
